<task id="060" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend PaneEventTypes.ts with MemoryPaneEvent interface (ADR-030 v2)</title>
    <phase>4: WP5 6-Tier Memory Subsystem (sub-WP 4a)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>055</dependencies>
    <blocks>061,062,063,064,098</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, typescript, ADR-030, ADR-015</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies binding ADR-030 v2 type surface; consumed cross-wave by 098 (ContextPane subscriber); typed payload correctness is load-bearing per ADR-015 tier-1 safety</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-A1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>CRIT-2 fix — single sequential edit to PaneEventTypes.ts so 4-A2 verifications and downstream 4-M (098) ContextPane subscriber both consume a stable type definition; type-channel union extension is atomic</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts` to add the `memory` channel and `MemoryPaneEvent` discriminated-union interface per ADR-030 v2 amendment (2026-06-21). The 5 initial discriminants are: `promotion_pending`, `promotion_resolved`, `fact_promoted`, `pin_added`, `pin_removed`. Extend `PaneChannel` from 4-member to 5-member closed union, and extend `PaneChannelEventMap` to map `memory` → `MemoryPaneEvent`. Payloads carry deterministic IDs + 80-char `factSummary` preview only per ADR-015 tier-1 safety — NEVER raw fact text.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform frontend developer. Expert in TypeScript discriminated unions, React event-bus typing, and ADR-030 PaneEventBus invariants.</role>

  <goal>
    `PaneEventTypes.ts` exports `MemoryPaneEvent` interface (5 discriminants per ADR-030 v2 § "memory channel payload reference"). `PaneChannel` is `'workspace' | 'context' | 'conversation' | 'safety' | 'memory'`. `PaneChannelEventMap['memory']` resolves to `MemoryPaneEvent`. Existing subscribers continue to compile (additive change). Type-check passes. The Spaarke.AI.Widgets barrel (`events/index.ts`) re-exports `MemoryPaneEvent` if barrel currently re-exports peer event interfaces.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md §6.4 (Promote-to-matter flow) and ADR-030 v2 amendment (this project, 2026-06-21). The 6-tier memory subsystem requires UI signals for the matter-memory promotion approval workflow. The reconciliation review initially namespaced these as `workspace.promotion_pending` inside the `workspace` channel; ADR-030 v2 elevates them to a dedicated `memory` channel because workspace-channel subscribers had to filter out non-workspace events. This task is the foundational type extension; downstream consumers (task 098 ContextPane subscriber, tasks 096/097 dispatch sites) depend on this type surface.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBus.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/index.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">Closed union of EXACTLY five members: `workspace | context | conversation | safety | memory`. Adding a sixth requires a successor ADR.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">5 initial `memory` discriminants per amendment record: `promotion_pending`, `promotion_resolved`, `fact_promoted`, `pin_added`, `pin_removed`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">Payloads MUST be typed via `PaneChannelEventMap`. NO `any` payloads.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 v2">Additive change — existing subscribers MUST continue to compile and run.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging safety: payloads carry deterministic IDs + `factSummary` (80-char preview) only. NEVER raw fact text, user message content, or recall results.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">Per architecture §6.4: `promotion_pending` includes `{ promotionId, factSummary (80-char), matterId, sessionId }`. `promotion_resolved` includes `{ promotionId, decision: 'approved'|'rejected', factId? }`. `fact_promoted` includes `{ factId, matterId, source }`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tenant scoping comes from subscriber context, NOT in payload (per ADR-030 v2 § "Constraints preserved" bullet 3).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts` end-to-end. Locate existing `PaneChannel` union, the four `*PaneEvent` interfaces, and the `PaneChannelEventMap` interface.</step>
    <step order="2">Add `MemoryPaneEvent` discriminated-union type per ADR-030 v2 § "memory channel payload reference" — exact 5 discriminants and field shapes from the ADR (do not add fields not in the ADR).</step>
    <step order="3">Extend `PaneChannel` union to add `'memory'` as 5th member.</step>
    <step order="4">Extend `PaneChannelEventMap` to add `memory: MemoryPaneEvent`.</step>
    <step order="5">Read `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/index.ts`. If existing peer event interfaces (WorkspacePaneEvent, ContextPaneEvent, etc.) are re-exported from the barrel, add `MemoryPaneEvent` re-export consistently. If barrel only re-exports the union types, no change needed.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/` if not already current.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npx tsc --noEmit` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/` to verify the type extension is valid and existing consumers still compile.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify `PaneEventBus.ts` does NOT need a code change (per ADR-030 v2 amendment § "Required implementation updates" bullet 2 — Set-keyed registry is channel-string-agnostic). Reading-only confirmation; task 061 covers this verification.</step>
    <step order="9">Run code-review + adr-check (FULL rigor Step 9.5 quality gates) — confirm ADR-030 v2 compliance + ADR-015 tier-1 payload safety.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 060 status → ✅; current-task.md → next task (061).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">PaneEventTypes.ts, PaneEventBus.ts, index.ts, ADR-030</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Apply type extension to PaneEventTypes.ts (and possibly index.ts)</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npm install / npx tsc --noEmit / npm run build</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Locate existing PaneChannel / PaneChannelEventMap usages to verify additive change is non-breaking</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts — MemoryPaneEvent added; PaneChannel extended; PaneChannelEventMap extended</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/index.ts (if barrel re-exports peer interfaces) — MemoryPaneEvent re-exported</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/060-paneeventtypes-extension.md — brief note on what shipped + downstream consumer guidance for 098/096/097</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`PaneChannel` exports as a 5-member closed union including `'memory'`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`MemoryPaneEvent` exports as discriminated-union with exactly 5 discriminants matching ADR-030 v2 payload reference.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`PaneChannelEventMap['memory']` resolves to `MemoryPaneEvent` (TypeScript type-level check).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0 in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No `any` type in `MemoryPaneEvent` payloads.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No raw fact text, user message content, or recall result fields in payloads (ADR-015 tier-1 safety).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`grep "MemoryPaneEvent" src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/` returns at minimum the type export and `PaneChannelEventMap` mapping.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test scope="type-check">`npx tsc --noEmit` — type extension is additive and non-breaking for existing consumers.</test>
    <test scope="lint">`npm run lint` (or `eslint`) in `Spaarke.AI.Widgets` package — no new lint errors.</test>
    <test scope="manual-smoke">Spot-check: open one canonical workspace consumer file (e.g., a WorkspacePane tab bar component) and verify it still type-checks against the extended `PaneChannel` union (no breaking change to `workspace`-channel handlers).</test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    This task is the foundational type extension consumed cross-wave by task 098 (ContextPane subscriber for `memory` channel). Main session enforces cross-wave dependency before dispatching 098. Per ADR-030 v2 amendment bullet 2: PaneEventBus.ts requires NO code change (channel registry is string-keyed). Task 061 verifies this in a separate read-only pass.
  </notes>

